Joseph Vaughan wrote:

&gt; This is almost certainly a classpath problem. 
&gt; 
&gt; A few common pitfalls:
&gt; 
&gt; Be sure to set your classpath to include the junit.jar (not just the
&gt; directory which contains it, you must type out the .jar name as well).  e.g.
&gt; D:&#92;myjars&#92;ajar.jar
&gt; 
&gt; Be sure that your classpath does not overlap your package names.
&gt; 
&gt; ie. My classpath is D:&#92;Openratings&#92;source&#92;java&#92;
&gt;     my package name is com&#92;openratings&#92;junit&#92;
&gt; 
&gt; The error your getting looks like your classpath is the equivelent of
&gt; D:&#92;Openratings&#92;source&#92;java&#92;com&#92;openratings&#92;junit&#92;.
&gt; 
&gt; The classloader looks in the classpath + the package name.
&gt; 
&gt; Hope that helps.
